---
import Base from '~/layouts/Base.astro';

// Replace these literals before publishing.
const HOSTER_NAME    = '{{HOSTER_NAME}}';        // e.g. 'Cloudflare, Inc.'
const HOSTER_URL     = '{{HOSTER_URL}}';         // e.g. 'https://www.cloudflare.com/'
const HOSTER_COUNTRY = '{{HOSTER_COUNTRY}}';     // e.g. 'United States'
const EMAIL          = '{{EMAIL}}';

// Last updated date — bump whenever this page is materially edited.
const LAST_UPDATED = 'April 2026';

const description =
  'Privacy policy under Art. 13 GDPR for Rouven Jahnke\u2019s personal academic website.';
---

<Base title="Privacy Policy" description={description}>
  <article class="prose" lang="en">
    <header class="page-header">
      <p class="page-header__eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy
        <span lang="de" style="font-style: italic; color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.6em;">(Datenschutzerklärung)</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="page-header__lede">
        Information about the processing of personal data when this
        website is accessed, in accordance with Art.&nbsp;13 of the
        General Data Protection Regulation
        (<abbr title="General Data Protection Regulation / DSGVO">GDPR</abbr>).
      </p>
    </header>

    <h2>1. Controller</h2>
    <p>
      The controller responsible for the processing of personal data
      within the meaning of Art.&nbsp;4 No.&nbsp;7 GDPR is the natural
      person identified in the <a href="/impressum">Legal Notice</a>.
      Contact for any privacy-related enquiry:
      <a href={`mailto:${EMAIL}`}>{EMAIL}</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Data collected when the site is accessed</h2>
    <p>
      When this website is accessed, the hosting provider processes
      technical access data on the server side in log files:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>IP address of the requesting device (typically truncated by the hoster)</li>
      <li>date and time of the request</li>
      <li>requested URL and HTTP status code</li>
      <li>amount of data transferred</li>
      <li>user agent (browser, operating system, language)</li>
      <li>referrer URL, if transmitted by the browser</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      This site uses <strong>no</strong> analytics, tracking, or
      profiling services. <strong>No cookies are set.</strong> There are
      no forms and no other data storage beyond the log data named
      above. Contact is made exclusively via the email address given in
      the Legal Notice; in that case the transmitted content is stored
      for the purpose of handling the enquiry.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Purpose and legal basis</h2>
    <p>
      The processing of log data serves the reliable operation, the
      stability and the security of the website, in particular the
      defence against abusive access. The legal basis is Art.&nbsp;6
      paragraph&nbsp;1&nbsp;lit.&nbsp;f GDPR; the legitimate interest
      arises from the purposes named above. For email contact the legal
      basis is Art.&nbsp;6 paragraph&nbsp;1&nbsp;lit.&nbsp;b
      respectively&nbsp;lit.&nbsp;f GDPR.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Recipients and processors</h2>
    <p>
      The website is hosted by <strong>{HOSTER_NAME}</strong>
      (<a href={HOSTER_URL} rel="external noopener">{HOSTER_URL}</a>),
      registered in {HOSTER_COUNTRY}.
      The hoster processes the data named under section&nbsp;2 as a
      processor within the meaning of Art.&nbsp;28 GDPR on the basis of
      a corresponding data processing agreement. No transfer to further
      third parties takes place.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Transfer to third countries</h2>
    <p>
      Where the hosting provider processes personal data in a third
      country outside the EU or the EEA, this is done on the basis of an
      adequacy decision (Art.&nbsp;45 GDPR) or appropriate safeguards,
      in particular the Standard Contractual Clauses of the European
      Commission (Art.&nbsp;46 paragraph&nbsp;2&nbsp;lit.&nbsp;c GDPR).
    </p>

    <h2>6. Storage period</h2>
    <p>
      Log data is stored within the hoster's customary retention period
      (typically a few days, at most a few weeks) and is then deleted or
      anonymised so that no personal reference remains. Email content
      is stored until the enquiry has been finally dealt with, and
      beyond that only insofar as statutory retention obligations
      require it.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      You have the right, at any time and vis-à-vis the controller, to:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>access information about the data processed about you (Art.&nbsp;15 GDPR)</li>
      <li>rectification of incorrect data (Art.&nbsp;16 GDPR)</li>
      <li>erasure (Art.&nbsp;17 GDPR)</li>
      <li>restriction of processing (Art.&nbsp;18 GDPR)</li>
      <li>data portability (Art.&nbsp;20 GDPR)</li>
      <li>object to processing (Art.&nbsp;21 GDPR)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      An informal message to the email address given in the
      <a href="/impressum">Legal Notice</a> is sufficient to exercise
      these rights.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority</h2>
    <p>
      You have the right to lodge a complaint with a data protection
      supervisory authority about the processing of your personal data
      (Art.&nbsp;77 GDPR). The authority with local jurisdiction over
      the controller is the
      <i>Hamburg Commissioner for Data Protection and Freedom of
      Information</i>:
    </p>
    <address>
      Der Hamburgische Beauftragte für<br />
      Datenschutz und Informationsfreiheit
      (<abbr lang="de" title="Hamburgischer Beauftragter für Datenschutz und Informationsfreiheit">HmbBfDI</abbr>)<br />
      Ludwig-Erhard-Straße 22, 7th floor<br />
      20459 Hamburg, Germany<br />
      Phone: +49&nbsp;40&nbsp;428&nbsp;54-4040<br />
      Email: <a href="mailto:mailbox@datenschutz.hamburg.de">mailbox@datenschutz.hamburg.de</a><br />
      Web: <a href="https://datenschutz-hamburg.de" rel="external noopener">datenschutz-hamburg.de</a>
    </address>
    <p>
      You may also lodge a complaint with the supervisory authority of
      your habitual residence, place of work, or the place of the
      alleged infringement.
    </p>

    <h2>9. No automated decision-making</h2>
    <p>
      No automated decision-making or profiling within the meaning of
      Art.&nbsp;22 GDPR takes place on this site.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      This policy may be updated when the technical setup of the
      website or the legal situation changes. The version currently in
      force is always available at <code>/privacy</code>; the
      <em>last updated</em> line below is bumped on every material
      change.
    </p>

    <hr />
    <p>
      <small>Last updated: {LAST_UPDATED}.</small>
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
